                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13551188" author="ssevertson" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 15:33:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For context, we ran into this on our CI server, where core was not included as a test runtime dependency. Obviously, our apps will be deployed with core &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13555992" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2013 08:53:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if this can be fixed but I will investigate it.  The Log4j 1.2 bridge has methods on the Category such as getting the parent logger that are currently implemented but would have to be noops if they go to the Log4j 2 API only. FWIW if you build the site you would now see that the Log4j 1.2 bridge says it needs both the API and implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13568856" author="ssevertson" created="Fri, 1 Feb 2013 16:34:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As long as the documentation is clear, I think this can be closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
